 0370:     """Calculate the GWB from an eccentric SAM evolution model.
 0371: 
 0372:     This function uses the precomputed binary-evolution of eccentricities over some range of separations.
 0373:     This assumes a single eccentricity evolution e(a) for all binaries.
 0374:     Redshifts are assumed to stay constant during this evolution.
 0375: 
 0376:     h_c^2 = (dn/dz) * h_{s,n}^2 * 4*pi*c * d_c^2 * (1+z) * tau
 0377: 
 0378:     h_{s,n}^2 = (32 / 5) * c^-8 * (2/n)^2 * (G Mchirp)^(10/3) * d_c^-2 * (2*pi*forb_r)^(4/3) * g(n,e)
 0379:               = GW_SRC_CONST^2 * (2/n)^2 * Mchirp^(10/3) * d_c^-2 * forb_r^(4/3) * g(n,e)
 0380: 
 0381:

 0610:     """Calculate the GWB from an eccentric SAM evolution model.
 0611: 
 0612:     This function uses the precomputed binary-evolution of eccentricities over some range of separations.
 0613:     This assumes a single eccentricity evolution e(a) for all binaries.
 0614:     Redshifts are assumed to stay constant during this evolution.
 0615: 
 0616:     Parameters
 0617:     ----------
 0618:     ndens : (double ***)
 0619:         3D array specifying the SAM number-density of binaries in each bin, in total-mass, mass-ratio, and redshift.
 0620:         This is typically `sam.static_binary_density`, corresponding to 'd^3 n / [dlog10M dq dz]' in units of [Mpc^-3].
 0621:     mtot_log10 : (double *)
 0622:         Array of log10 values of the total-mass (in grams) grid edges in the SAM model.  i.e. `log10(sam.mtot)`.
 0623:     mrat : (double *)
 0624:         Array of mass-ratio grid edges in the SAM model.  i.e. `sam.mrat`.
 0625:     redz : (double *)
